        <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
            <head id="a4" altrender="biography">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
            <p>Professor Abraham (Al) Nash was born on September 16, 1915 in Baltimore, MD, into a
                working-class family of Italian and Russian immigrants. Late in life he earned a
                B.A. from Columbia College, an M.A. from New York University, and a Ph.D. in
                Sociology from Columbia University. </p>
            <p>Professor Nash was a taught in the New York State School of Industrial and Labor
                Relations New York City Extension Office from 1966 until his retirement in 1985.
                Prior to that he had been a shop steward, business agent, and local union president
                for the UAW. Other unions he worked with include: the Electrical Workers Union,
                AFSCME District Council 37, Taxi Drivers Union, the Musicians Union, and Local 1199. </p>
            <p>Professor Nash died on August 3, 1996.</p>
        </bioghist>
